<p>I am currently sending a Jasper Report (invoice) by email with javax mail. It works fine :</p>  <pre><code>InputStream reportStream; reportStream = this.getClass().getResourceAsStream(TEMPLATE_INVOICE);  JasperDesign jd;  jd = JRXmlLoader.load(reportStream); JasperReport jr = JasperCompileManager.compileReport(jd); for (Long invoiceId:invoicesId){     List&lt;Object[]&gt; results = invoiceRepository.findAllByIdInvoice(invoiceId);     JasperPrint jp = JasperFillManager.fillReport(jr, new HashMap&lt;String,Object&gt;(), dataProvider.getInvoice(results));      ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();     JasperExportManager.exportReportToPdfStream(jp, baos);     mailService.sendMail(baos); } </code></pre>  <p>Now I would like to send a zip containing all my invoices by email.<br> At each iteration I would add the generated jasper report into a zip file, and then I would send this zip by email.<br> Is there a way to do that? </p>  <p>Thanks</p>